<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-08-24T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-08-24T15:00:00-05:00" n="833" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d833">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.5914/115</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Minister <persName type="to">Egan</persName>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Departmemt of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-08-24T15:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">August 24, 1916, 3 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>155. Your 323, August 23d, 4 p.m. So far as I know, no such question
                                has been put to the President, and I am certain no official of the
                                Department has made any statement of the kind indicated. So far as I
                                know, there is nothing to indicate that the Senate will not approve
                                the treaty before adjournment.</p>
                            <p>You may use this information in your discretion to counteract any
                                impression that the treaty may not be ratified during the present
                                session.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>